The paper deals with the problem of designing low latency and low complexity schemes for channel state feedback over the MIMO-MAC, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes separated source-channel schemes and joint source-channel schemes, which are related to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses a code design based on scalar quantization and uncoded QAM modulation, which is related to communication (cs.COM).
